Change the way non-default [effective\_io\_concurrency](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/13/runtime-config-resource.html#GUC-EFFECTIVE-IO-CONCURRENCY) values affect concurrency (Thomas Munro) 

Previously, this value was adjusted before setting the number of concurrent requests. The value is now used directly. Conversion of old values to new ones can be done using:

SELECT round(sum(_`OLDVALUE`_ / n::float)) AS newvalue FROM generate_series(1, _`OLDVALUE`_) s(n);
